IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The Organization's mission is to improve the health and well-being of pregnant women, infants, and young children in Sarasota County.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The Organization's mission is to improve the health and well-being of pregnant women, infants, and young children in Sarasota County.
IRS990.Desc: Healthy Start Care Coordination - Professional case management of pregnant women and infants who are at risk for adverse outcomes (fetal death, prematurity, low birth weight, and infant death). Includes home visiting, education, support, and referrals to additional specialized services.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Healthy Start Wrap Around Services - Specialized services for pregnant women and infants in Healthy Start who need additional education and counseling for risks that could lead to poor birth outcomes.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Other services - Prenatal care counseling for pregnant women who have Medicaid insurance. Providing information, follow-up, and referrals. Community based education and support for African-American pregnant women who are at risk for poor birth outcomes. Project to examine fetal and infant death and identify trends in causes of death or low birth weight. Providing free educational information and access to community resources for pregnant women and new parents.

The Organization's donor restricted endowment is to be held in perpetuity with interest to support the Save My Life Program.

The Coalition has received a determination letter of tax-exempt status under section 501c3 of the Internal Revenue Code and Chapter 220.13 of the Florida Statutes, respectively. Management is not aware of any activities that would jeopardize the Coalition's tax-exempt status. The Coalition is not aware of any tax position at has taken that are subject to a significant degree of uncertainty. Tax years after June 30, 2018 remains subject to examination by taxing authorities.
Individuals can become members by volunteer or request.
The voting members elect the Board annually.Individuals can become members by volunteer or request.

The Board Chair conducts performance reviews of the Executive Director, and signs a salary change form which is submitted to the payroll company. Salary is based on comparable positions in the region.

The Executive Director conducts performance reviews of all employees, utilizing a standardized protocol for determining salary increases. Every one to two years, a review of salaries for comparable positions in the region is done to determine if changes in salary bands are needed.
Form 1023 and Form 990 available upon request. 990 also available on Guidestar.
Governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements are available to the public upon request.
The draft of the Form 990 is distributed to the Board of Directors for review prior to submission to the IRS with a reasonable deadline to return any comments.
A member of the Executive Committee follows up on submision of the conflict of interest statements.
